Russia to Sow 30.2 Million Hectares With Spring Grains, IFX Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-03-29T08:37:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/russia-to-sow-30-2-million-hectares-with-spring-grains-ifx-says.html
Russia will sow 30.2 million
hectares (74.6 million acres) with spring grains this year,
about 1.7 million hectares more than last year, Interfax
reported, citing the Agriculture Ministry.  The country planted 15.5 million hectares with winter
grains in 2010, of which 13.9 million hectares, or 90 percent,
are graded “good and satisfactory,” the news service said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 